## Performance — Deferred Tool Loading

Add this to your `.claude/settings.json` to save ~14,000 tokens per turn:

```json
{
  "env": {
    "ENABLE_TOOL_SEARCH": "true"
  }
}
```

This loads only 6 primary tools upfront and lazy-loads the rest on demand. Starting context drops from ~45K to ~20K tokens. The single highest-ROI config change you can make.

## Cache Efficiency Rules
1. Never add one-off permissions to global settings — use project-level
2. Never change tools/models mid-session — use subagents
3. Don't edit this file mid-session — put updates in messages
4. Static content first, dynamic last
5. Enable `ENABLE_TOOL_SEARCH` for deferred tool loading (see above)

## Rules
1. Never delete files without asking — archive or rename
2. Git commit frequently with conventional commits
3. Secrets: never hardcode — use env vars
4. Skills: check `SKILLS-INDEX.md` before building from scratch
5. Bug fixes: write reproduction test FIRST, then fix, then operationalize
6. Decisions: use dialectic review for anything expensive to reverse
